##The diary of a psychologist (week 2)

Health insight

Functional introduction, understand the health professional news

On February 9, Tang Wei, director of the Department of Mental Psychology of Wenzhou Kangning Hospital Group, arrived in Wuhan with the Third Group of Zhejiang medical team from Hubei Province to participate in the psychological crisis intervention in the front line of Wuhan's fight against the epidemic and provide psychological assistance to medical staff and patients.

During the period, director Tang Wei in the diary to record the medical staff to overcome difficulties, fighting against the epidemic front-line experience. At eight o'clock, after obtaining the consent of the author, the extracts are compiled and published in stages.

Protection training before entering the shelter

Sunday February 16 Sunny Wuhan

Yesterday, a heavy snow, let the weather more cold, but also make the outside air more fresh, look out of the window snow, director Liu Zhihong and I got up early, eat a little breakfast rushed to the outside, afraid of beautiful scenery was destroyed. We've been here for six days, and we've been through a lot of life-changing stuff, and we've been doing stuff in our room for five days, and it's really hard to come out, and we're taking advantage of the fact that we don't have anything to do right now, so we're just kind of taking a break. Director Liu's childlike mind was attracted by the charming scenery, only to take photos, let me also be his model once.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The afternoon atmosphere suddenly tense, began training into the cabin before the protection, for me and director Liu Zhihong, it is really difficult. The two of US had never been exposed to the suits, had never been in an infectious disease ward, and our only knowledge was the video of the last few days. After listening to the training, we were dumbfounded, in and out of the cabin to the hotel room need four coats, came in a hurry without time to prepare, I only took one set, director Liu took two sets, together also not enough standard requirements.

We decided to optimize the resources, two people together, three coats and a pair of cotton underwear each, finally enough supplies. Decided I'd go first. He stayed in bed while I was gone. Ideal is beautiful, the reality is skinny. When I tried it on, I realized that his pants were a skirt, and he couldn't wear my pants.

If you have difficulty finding an organization, call the hospital immediately and let them know your needs. Wife and Wang Hongyue general manager in the first time to prepare, and told tomorrow sent. It's nice to have an organization.

Open a hotline and work 24 hours a day

Monday, February 17 fine Wuhan

Morning to look out the window, watching the team members to and from work, can not help but worry about impatience. One is to worry about the crew's health, the first day into the shelter experience, protection can do well. Second, for the psychological fear of the team members, go to the shelter and in the shelter outside is completely different. Looking at my worry, director Liu talked to me in a professional manner and told me that they had to learn to accept it when they came here. The two brothers chat, the road side of the Magpie Kept Chirping, is it good to come? I can't imagine.

I hadn't decided how to accept myself yet. Someone from the headquarters picked us up and moved us to the Vienna Hotel, the headquarters of the Zhejiang aid team. So director Liu and I packed our bags as quickly as possible. You know, we've moved three times in seven days, and we're not moving, we're on our way. Empty bus carrying me and director Liu to a new journey.

Arriving at the Hotel Vienna, we found that the protection here is much higher than that of our hotel in the Magnolia Prairie. We should take our body temperature no matter when we go in or out, and we should set it strictly according to the polluted area, semi-polluted area and clean area, we do not dare to cross the line half step, carefully back to the room, according to the Gourd Gourd Gourd Gourd Gourd Gourd Gourd Gourd Gourd Gourd Gourd Gourd put their own room is divided into three districts.

In the evening, Zhejiang Province aid Hubei Brigade Captain Chen summoned me and director Liu to his room, we know in our hearts there is a task. Captain Chen, who has forty + years of experience in the Infectious Diseases Department, briefed us on the current situation and told us that we are too old to enter the shelter. At present, the team members are in a state of anxiety. We should increase the level of psychological assistance to prevent accidents from happening, to solve the individual psychological problems in the embryonic, do a good job in the shelter of the patient's comfort work, can be carried out in a variety of ways, any problem to find the organization to solve.

In the evening and director Liu Zhihong more extensive open hotline, the implementation of 24-hour working system.

I've had a lot of colds in my life, and this one's the worst

Tuesday February 18th Fine Wuhan

Today is a busy day, a psychologist, psychiatrist, in order to do the medical staff's psychological intervention video, was forced to live sound engineer, typesetter, editor, cameraman, text editor, you also need to know how to answer questions from reporters and how to keep in touch with the rear. In the limited time, but also to answer online questions, answer the questions inside the Shelter Hospital.

It seems that intervention requires all-round talents, we are going to be abandoned by the Times, all of this for my two old people are new things, have to learn. Fortunately, my two learning ability is strong, one can learn.

Director Liu drew up a work plan and put it into each shelter. From the afternoon to the evening, many obvious things were happening, mainly the fatigue and insomnia of the medical staff in the shelter. The patients were just nervous and restless, repeatedly asking themselves whether they had won a new crown, if there's a cure, if you'RE GONNA die.

Because of too many problems, director Liu and I type slowly, two people have to use voice, each computer, two mobile phones to charge in turn.

Now it is mainly to boost morale, encourage the team members and strengthen spiritual construction. My Essay has been edited into a video, which has been well received and forwarded by Xu Yi, a teacher with the public number of the Zhejiang psychological therapy committee.

It's time to reveal a secret today.

The next day in Wuhan, due to the cold weather, coupled with our constantly moving, security problems, I have a cold symptoms, headache dizziness, runny nose, fortunately no increase in body temperature.

I didn't dare say anything. I knew what I'd look like if anyone knew. First, I would immediately quarantine. Second, cause unnecessary panic. Third, to the team members and leaders added to the trouble. Fourth, send me back or not, the leadership to consider. Fifth, how to send me back more trouble, here closed, there is no way out. Sixth, the unit knows that the leadership is more nervous. Seven, the family know how to do, they can bear it?

Fortunately, after confirmation, I do not have a new coronary pneumonia, it should be a cold.

I've had a million colds in my life, but this one was the most wrenching, the most thought-provoking.

Director Liu is really a psychological big shot, see my mood, asked me how, I told him to keep a secret, now I basically do not go out in the room, all living materials by him to give me protection, report to him twice a day body temperature.

I suddenly feel very sad, I am a psychiatrist / Professor, a psychologist, and a member of the Zhejiang Provincial Hubei aid team. Now I am suddenly isolated from myself. Fortunately, I can work in a room without disturbing others, i also experience the new coronary pneumonia patients and the psychological isolation of the psychological.

A few days to experience a lot of their own, director Liu n times a day of questions, his answer (the outside world leads to more anxiety) , his regular daily temperature, sometimes two or three times, repeated check (forced formation) ; Constantly checking to see if you have new pneumonia (mind-numbing, obsessive thoughts) ; a bad night's sleep, lots of dreams, nightmares (insomnia, underlying anxiety) ; a poor appetite, not wanting to eat (somatic symptoms) ; headaches, dizziness, and constant feeling of sore throat (conversion symptoms) . Especially in the nose 24 hours have a strange smell, the smell of disinfectant, in fact, I know, my balcony three sides air, there is no possibility of such a smell, this is the conversion symptoms.

I kept saying to myself, it doesn't matter. Wash your face with cold water three times a day, before going to bed at night with hot water to wash sweat to sleep, every day in the room exercise, sit quietly, meditation, is not high body temperature, because every day to report body temperature.

But these are not great for my mental relaxation, director Liu said my potential anxiety appeared, I do not admit. I participated in the 2008 Wenchuan County earthquake relief, is the first batch in; presided over the Wenzhou 7.23 bullet train accident, presided over the Wenzhou post-typhoon psychological intervention... psychological quality is not strong. But I always do, those psychological quality is not good, and did not know the severity of the epidemic, psychological or mental collapse, based on the above considerations, I predict that after the epidemic psychological problems will be prominent. Panic is worse than a virus.

Through their own examples, I think, are the telephone, Wechat to do intervention, the effect of how much? Do the results that some of us have here, with the Scales, tell the story? My strong psychology, in addition to director Liu Zhihong's strong intervention, also seems to have little effect, so that tension, anxiety, insomnia this is a normal reaction, to accept, to divert attention.

On a snowy morning. Director Liu took me out to play a circle, suddenly miraculously found that what symptoms are not. That's the power of movement and movement.

Let's Love Sports. Exercise relieves anxiety.

A patient with severe anxiety

Wednesday February 19 fine Wuhan

A busy day, leading to dizziness, a few days before the work plan was approved, director Liu and I obviously busy up. There is a psychological group here, made up of nurses with psychological counseling certificates, who can get into the shelter, which makes a bridge between director Liu and me. There's a lot of feedback, so let's take it one at a time.

They reported that a patient had severe anxiety, was not adapted to the environment in the shelter, fainted, did not receive much assistance, was a problem in the shelter, but was also representative, and that solving her problem could provide us with some experience.

After consulting with director Liu Zhihong, I will intervene and he will be the supervisor.

On the phone, the first thing the patient says is, "Dr. Tang, I know you. ". Hear this sentence, I know I and director Liu early work has been effective, this no doubt shorten our distance, but also increased compliance.

After learning that the husband of the patient had a fever and cough two days before her, he was found to be in the hospital with a positive result of new coronary pneumonia. He himself also had a fever and cough the next day. He was afraid that he was also suffering from new coronary pneumonia and requested isolation on his own initiative, was sent to the present shelter hospital, to the hospital only to find that he was not with her husband (psychological gap) ; Home Children Can Not Cook, also at home isolation, children do not eat (reality anxiety) ; My in-laws were in hospital before I was admitted to the hospital. I didn't know who was taking care of them now. I had anxiety before. I was repelled by sound. I couldn't stand loud sounds. I was sensitive to light, once in the hospital to take care of my father-in-law, in the hospital corridor to see a lot of people, they fainted, feel gas can not come out, want to die feeling, body discomfort, sweating, very afraid (panic attack) .

After a quick assessment, a "solution" is given, summed up as follows:

1. Discuss the current outbreak and quarantine policy with them, show understanding and support for quarantine (psychological support, find inner motivation and develop your potential) .

2. Call other people in your home who are not segregated or village officials to find out about your in-laws and express your desire for help.

3. Make a video call with your child, teach them how to make some simple foods, and tell them that this will improve their hands-on ability to change from passive to active (reverse thinking, focus on positive) . The patient is happy to accept that this can change the child's ability to operate.

4. Tell people that they are afraid of voices and that they are fainting because they have a preexisting anxiety disorder that may induce panic attacks. Explain the causes and manifestations of panic attacks and how to deal with them.

5. Tell her to report her rejection of sound to the nurse, tell her when music is playing in the shelter hospital, prepare her to move away from the bullhorn and consider changing beds (externally) if possible.

6, Photophobia, can sleep at night, wear a blindfold (reduce external stimulation) .

7. Meditate or abdominal breathing before bedtime (relaxation exercises) , which feedback says is helpful.

Tell yourself and director Liu's contact information, let them have problems at any time contact (guarantee) .

9. Consider low doses of Diazepam if you don't reject the drug (there are other ways to ensure this) .

10. Smile and tell your doctor, much better.

We are happy to be recognized by the patients, after all, we are here to help them, but this can not face-to-face intervention, leading us to spend many times more time, usually we are slow and unskilled in typing, that caused both of his fingers to Chafe. But in order to help more people, bite the bullet.

Into Wuhan's largest shelter hospital

Friday, February 21st, Wuhan, cloudy

Do Not Know How many days to stay in the room, do not know what day of the week, every day is to answer the phone, back Wechat, sometimes do not know what time, tired to look out the window, the outside world is wonderful, the outside world is very helpless. Now the most difficult is not to see the sun, their own room can not shine in.

Every day and director Liu Zhihong Wechat to discuss work content and case exchanges, although a wall, but because the epidemic can not face-to-face, it can only use this method of communication. It's a simple matter of going back and forth several times and wasting a lot of time.

At 3:45 pm, Captain Chen called and told me and director Liu to assemble in the first floor lobby. Excited and excited, waiting for this moment. Hurry up and get dressed and meet downstairs.

After getting on the bus, Captain Chen once again gave us the popularization of knowledge, safety, safety, and then safety. Told me and director Liu's task is to protect the psychological safety of all medical staff, the other is the mental health of the patients in the shelter. Doing something meaningful can actually help the patient.

Thirty five minutes later, we arrived at the largest shelter hospital in Wuhan: Rihai Shelter Hospital, where the staff was still busy, working overtime, a scene of bustling activity.

We took over the largest C cabin with 1,400 beds. On the way, we met the leaders of the Wuhan Municipal Party Committee and listened to our plan for psychological assistance to the hospital.

When we entered the shelter, we found that it was completely different. There were four sections A, B, C and D. each section was divided into lots of compartments. Each compartment had 20 beds. A nurse had 40 beds. Inside the conditions are very good, washing Gargle, toilet, bathroom, reading room, TV everything. Better condition and equipment than any other shelter hospital.

Director Liu and I, based on the scene, decided to arrange a psychological station, to answer the patient's questions, and patients form a link. The problem is that, according to the epidemiology, the incidence of schizophrenia is 4.6 per 1,000, so patients with severe mental illness are likely to appear in the shelter. Once these patients appear here, the management here will certainly increase the difficulties, this is the problem that director Liu and I are worried about.

At 8:00, we go back to the hotel, it's very sterile, whoever comes in must be killed, and everyone must go through a special tunnel, no crossing the line.

The lantern, I continue to answer the phone, back to Wechat, thinking about the direction of work tomorrow.

Another anxious family in isolation

Saturday, February 22, cloudy in Wuhan

Every day dealing with the psychological help of the patients in the shelter hospital, every time it makes me feel sad and makes me cry. I know as a psychologist I can't cry, but how can we settle down in this situation.

Every day and director Liu can only through the phone, wechat contact, all things can only through these links, with him in our mutual consultation.

Today is our 14th day here. In the past, it was time to rotate, but as things stand, there is no way. Doctors and nurses too many, the national elite, then round, where to find so many people? It's a national effort now. We're GONNA be short on follow-up. Besides, we're all going back in 14-day quarantine, so there's no one left to fill the gap.

Inexplicably Homesick, think of his daughter, wife, his mother, sisters, they are concerned about me every day, but the epidemic is not over, I can not go back. I can't be a deserter. Adhere to, here need me, here people also need me to adhere to here, believe that winter will pass, Spring will certainly come. In the spring, we'll look at the cherry blossoms.

The team gave me a psych patient this afternoon, and he's in the Magnolia prairie shelter. Nervous, anxious, sometimes crying.

Here are some examples:

37-year-old male, married, one female

About January 28, I had a sore throat, but I did not pay attention, because I had a sore throat since childhood, thought that is his problem, did not care too much. February 5th fever, all night fever, daytime fever, and diarrhea for a week, I felt that there may be problems, so I went to the hospital for a CT examination, said I was new pneumonia, let me quarantine at home, but the hospital has no beds, 6 let me go to the hotel quarantine, six or seven days in a quarantine hotel, no symptoms, but I was sent back to the shelter.

On the 12th, the wife, daughter and parents were all quarantined (there was one person in the house and the whole family had to be quarantined) , but they were quarantined in another hotel.

I'm so worried they're gonNA get infected, I can't call them, I can't listen to them, I'm scared. Dad tested positive for nucleic acid, and I'm even more scared, and I think it's all my fault, and it wouldn't have happened if I wasn't home, and I want to die.

At home, I live in a private house, which is built in my own home. I live on the first floor by myself. I don't usually have contact with them, but I don't know that I have this disease, so I don't think much about it. I went to the supermarket several times and didn't wear a mask, i think that's when I got it.

Now Dad was sent to the Chinese hospital nucleic acid test positive, CT test negative, I am now most worried about my daughter. I walk up and down every day can not stop, a stop to think, palms, feet, back is sweaty, heart rate accelerated, sleep at night, I think who can help me.

I'm afraid to call my wife right now, and when I do, she blames me for putting them in isolation, and I feel guilty.

Every time I miss them (crying) , I don't even have the courage to look at their pictures, my daughter called to say that she misses me, I will hang up the phone, I can't stop crying, can't stop.
